sqlViews.name: CdD - export Anacod 2020
sqlViews.sqlQuery:
WITH anacodsource AS (
         SELECT analytics_event_jo4aktbheqq.yearly AS year,
            analytics_event_jo4aktbheqq."nf91S8RgCEB" AS code,
            analytics_event_jo4aktbheqq."Fm6cUmmiY3d" AS age,
            analytics_event_jo4aktbheqq."cgYpqCgnVF2" AS sex
           FROM analytics_event_jo4aktbheqq
           where analytics_event_jo4aktbheqq.yearly = '2020'
        ), codes AS (
         SELECT anacodsource.code,
            anacodsource.sex
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (anacodsource.code IS NOT NULL)
          GROUP BY anacodsource.code, anacodsource.sex
          ORDER BY anacodsource.code
        )
 SELECT 'AAA'::text AS code,
        CASE
            WHEN (codes.sex = 'MALE'::text) THEN 1
            WHEN (codes.sex = 'FEMALE'::text) THEN 2
            ELSE 9
        END AS sex,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (anacodsource.sex = codes.sex)) AS "all",
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE ((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age = (0)::double precision))) AS age_0,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (1)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (4)::double precision))) AS age_1_4,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (5)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (9)::double precision))) AS age_5_9,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (10)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (14)::double precision))) AS age_10_14,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (15)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (19)::double precision))) AS age_15_19,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (20)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (24)::double precision))) AS age_20_24,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (25)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (29)::double precision))) AS age_25_29,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (30)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (34)::double precision))) AS age_30_34,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (35)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (39)::double precision))) AS age_35_39,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (40)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (44)::double precision))) AS age_40_44,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (45)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (49)::double precision))) AS age_45_49,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (50)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (54)::double precision))) AS age_50_54,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (55)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (59)::double precision))) AS age_55_59,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (60)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (64)::double precision))) AS age_60_64,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (65)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (69)::double precision))) AS age_65_69,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (70)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (74)::double precision))) AS age_70_74,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (75)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (79)::double precision))) AS age_75_79,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (80)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (84)::double precision))) AS age_80_84,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (85)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (89)::double precision))) AS age_85_89,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (90)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (94)::double precision))) AS age_90_94,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE ((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age >= (95)::double precision))) AS age_95plus,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE ((anacodsource.sex = codes.sex) AND (anacodsource.age IS NULL))) AS age_unknown
   FROM codes group by sex
UNION ALL
 SELECT codes.code,
        CASE
            WHEN (codes.sex = 'MALE'::text) THEN 1
            WHEN (codes.sex = 'FEMALE'::text) THEN 2
            ELSE 9
        END AS sex,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE ((anacodsource.code = codes.code) AND (anacodsource.sex = codes.sex))) AS "all",
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE (((anacodsource.code = codes.code) AND (anacodsource.sex = codes.sex)) AND (anacodsource.age = (0)::double precision))) AS age_0,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE ((((anacodsource.code = codes.code) AND (anacodsource.sex = codes.sex)) AND (anacodsource.age >= (1)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (4)::double precision))) AS age_1_4,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE ((((anacodsource.code = codes.code) AND (anacodsource.sex = codes.sex)) AND (anacodsource.age >= (5)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (9)::double precision))) AS age_5_9,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE ((((anacodsource.code = codes.code) AND (anacodsource.sex = codes.sex)) AND (anacodsource.age >= (10)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (14)::double precision))) AS age_10_14,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE ((((anacodsource.code = codes.code) AND (anacodsource.sex = codes.sex)) AND (anacodsource.age >= (15)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (19)::double precision))) AS age_15_19,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource
          WHERE ((((anacodsource.code = codes.code) AND (anacodsource.sex = codes.sex)) AND (anacodsource.age >= (20)::double precision)) AND (anacodsource.age <= (24)::double precision))) AS age_20_24,
    ( SELECT count(*) AS count
           FROM anacodsource

sqlViews.description: Termes du dictionnaire des causes de décès avec codes ICD, à utiliser avec le logiciel de codage IRIS.
sqlViews.name: CdD - Termes du dictionnaire avec ICD (pour IRIS)

sqlViews.description: Entrées de dictionnaire qui ne suivent pas le format standard de ICD-SMoL|ICD10|INDEX
sqlViews.name: CdD - entrées de dictionnaire avec un format de code non valide
sqlViews.sqlQuery:
select 
	nom,code 
from 
	optionvalue 
where 
	optionsetid in (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY_FR') and
	code != '[NON AFFICHÉ]' and 
	code not like '%|%|%'
order by sort_order;

sqlViews.description: Répertorie le prochain numéro d'index à utiliser lors de l'ajout de nouvelles entrées au dictionnaire.
sqlViews.name: CdD - numéro d'index du dictionnaire suivant
sqlViews.sqlQuery:
select 
	left(split_part(code, '|', 3), length(split_part(code, '|', 3)) - 5) as "type de terme",
	lpad((1+max(right(split_part(code, '|', 3), 5)::int))::text, 5, '0') as "valeur suivante"
from 
	optionvalue 
where 
	optionsetid = (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY_FR') and
	code like '5%|%|%' and
        left(split_part(code, '|', 3), length(split_part(code, '|', 3)) - 5) != 'INT_FR'
group by "type de terme";

sqlViews.description: Entrées de dictionnaire où le code ICD-SMoL ne fait pas référence à une entrée dans la liste ICD-SMoL.
sqlViews.name: CdD - entrées de dictionnaire avec référence ICD-SMoL non valide
sqlViews.sqlQuery:
select 
	nom,
	code, 
	split_part(code, '|', 1) as icd_smol
from 
	optionvalue 
where 
	optionsetid in (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY_FR') and
	split_part(code, '|', 1) not in (select code from optionvalue where optionsetid in (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL')) and
	code != '[NON AFFICHÉ]'
order by icd_smol;

sqlViews.description: Répertorie les entrées du dictionnaire dans lesquelles le code ICD-SMoL référencé est utilisé à la fois au niveau principal et au niveau de la sous-catégorie en même temps. Cela peut conduire à un double comptage lors de l'analyse.
sqlViews.name: CdD - entrées de dictionnaire mélangeant des catégories principales et des sous-catégories
sqlViews.sqlQuery:
WITH temptable AS (
select 
	optsub.name,
	optsub.code
from 
	optionvalue optsub
left join
	optionvalue optmain on 
	split_part(optsub.code, '.', 1) = split_part(optmain.code, '|', 1)

where 
	optsub.optionsetid = (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY_FR') and 
	optsub.code like '%.%|%|%' and
	optmain.optionsetid = (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY_FR') and 
	optmain.code not like '%.%|%|%'
group by
	optsub.name,
	optsub.code
union all
select 
	optmain.name,
	optmain.code
from 
	optionvalue optsub
left join
	optionvalue optmain on 
	split_part(optsub.code, '.', 1) = split_part(optmain.code, '|', 1)

where 
	optsub.optionsetid = (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY_FR') and 
	optsub.code like '%.%|%|%' and
	optmain.optionsetid = (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY_FR') and 
	optmain.code not like '%.%|%|%'
group by
	optmain.name,
	optmain.code
)
SELECT name as nom, code as code FROM temptable;

sqlViews.name: CdD - Termes introuvables dans le dictionnaire
sqlViews.sqlQuery:
WITH termtemp(terme) AS (
  SELECT 
    upper(eventdatavalues -> 'RLPSwlZI8ll' ->> 'value') AS terme,
    count(distinct(eventdatavalues -> 'RLPSwlZI8ll' ->> 'value')) AS compte
  FROM
    programstageinstance
  WHERE
    programstageinstance.programstageid = (SELECT programstageid FROM programstage WHERE programstage.uid ='wmSb9TmevMn')
  AND
    eventdatavalues -> 'CHYn3Y8YUjK' ->> 'value' = '[NON AFFICHÉ]'
  AND
    eventdatavalues -> 'RLPSwlZI8ll' ->> 'value' IS NOT NULL
  GROUP BY terme
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 
    upper(eventdatavalues -> 'EJRqgkUWbtq' ->> 'value') AS terme,
    count(distinct(eventdatavalues -> 'EJRqgkUWbtq' ->> 'value')) AS compte
  FROM
    programstageinstance
  WHERE
    programstageinstance.programstageid = (SELECT programstageid FROM programstage WHERE programstage.uid ='wmSb9TmevMn')
  AND
    eventdatavalues -> 'CHYn3Y8YUjK' ->> 'value' = '[NON AFFICHÉ]'
  AND
    eventdatavalues -> 'EJRqgkUWbtq' ->> 'value' IS NOT NULL
  GROUP BY terme
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 
    upper(eventdatavalues -> 'I672Kv6Leb6' ->> 'value') AS terme,
    count(distinct(eventdatavalues -> 'I672Kv6Leb6' ->> 'value')) AS compte
  FROM
    programstageinstance
  WHERE
    programstageinstance.programstageid = (SELECT programstageid FROM programstage WHERE programstage.uid ='wmSb9TmevMn')
  AND
    eventdatavalues -> 'CHYn3Y8YUjK' ->> 'value' = '[NON AFFICHÉ]'
  AND
    eventdatavalues -> 'I672Kv6Leb6' ->> 'value' IS NOT NULL
  GROUP BY terme
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 
    upper(eventdatavalues -> 'doSQuLwznxE' ->> 'value') AS terme,
    count(distinct(eventdatavalues -> 'doSQuLwznxE' ->> 'value')) AS compte
  FROM
    programstageinstance
  WHERE
    programstageinstance.programstageid = (SELECT programstageid FROM programstage WHERE programstage.uid ='wmSb9TmevMn')
  AND
    eventdatavalues -> 'CHYn3Y8YUjK' ->> 'value' = '[NON AFFICHÉ]'
  AND
    eventdatavalues -> 'doSQuLwznxE' ->> 'value' IS NOT NULL
  GROUP BY terme
)
SELECT * FROM termtemp
  GROUP BY terme, compte
  ORDER BY terme;
